; CCON audit B1 - stale paint extent carried across a moved anchor
;
; Run:   Execute S:ccon-b1
; Then:  type   Echo x >NIL:   and press Enter
; Then:  look at the row directly BELOW the echoed command.
;
;   BROKEN -> a 12-character gap punched into that row of #
;   FIXED  -> the row of # is unbroken
;
; Undo with:  Execute S:ccon-b1-off
;
; The prompt below is invisible on purpose: it is only a cursor
; move (CSI 7;999H). The column is clamped to the window width by
; csidispatch, so this parks the anchor exactly on the right margin
; whatever width the window is - that is the pending-wrap state the
; bug needs, without having to count characters.
Type S:ccon-b1-fill
Prompt "*e[7;999H"
